name: coding-standards
description: Enforce coding standards including Chinese comments, clean code principles, and premium UI specifications.
---

# Global Coding Standards & Skills

This skill defines the core development standards for this project. Use these guidelines for all code generation, refactoring, and UI design tasks.

## 1. 核心原则 (Core Principles)

*   **中文优先 (Chinese First)**:
    *   All code comments (single-line `//` and multi-line `/** ... */`), function descriptions, Git Commit Messages, and TODOs must be written in **Simplified Chinese (简体中文)**.
    *   Variable and function names remain in English (CamelCase/PascalCase).
*   **拒绝“屎山” (No Spaghetti Code)**:
    *   **File Length**: Limit single files (Components/Services) to 500 lines. Max 800 lines before mandatory refactoring.
    *   **Single Responsibility**: One function, one task. One component, one UI concern.
    *   **Decoupling**: Strictly separate Business Layout (Service), State (Context/Store), and UI (Component). Do not write complex API calls inside UI components.

## 2. 代码风格与规范 (Code Style)

### TypeScript
*   **No `any`**: Strictly forbidden unless absolutely necessary with a comment explaining why. Define Interfaces or Types for all structures.
*   **Explicit Types**: Explicitly declare types for Component Props, function parameters, and return values.

### React Components
*   **Functional Only**: Use Functional Components and Hooks exclusively.
*   **Custom Hooks**: Encapsulate complex side effects (`useEffect`) into Custom Hooks (e.g., `useAutoSave`, `useCanvasLogic`) to keep the main component clean.
*   **Performance**:
    *   Avoid unnecessary re-renders.
    *   Use `useMemo` for expensive calculations.
    *   Use `useCallback` when passing functions to children.

### 注释规范 (Comments)
*   **File Header**: Brief Chinese description at the top of each file.
*   **JSDoc**: All exported functions must have JSDoc-style comments in Chinese, describing parameters (`@param`) and return values (`@returns`).
*   **Self-Documenting**: Write code so clear that inline comments are rarely needed. Only comment on complex, non-obvious logic.

```typescript
/**
 * 计算画布自适应缩放比例
 * 根据当前窗口大小和节点边界，自动计算最佳 Scale 值
 * @param bounds 所有节点的边界矩形
 * @returns 推荐的 Zoom Level
 */
export function calculateFitZoom(bounds: BoundingBox): number {
    // ...
}
```

## 3. UI/UX 设计规范 (Design Specifications)

### 视觉风格 (Visual Aesthetics)
*   **Design Tokens**: Do not hardcode colors (e.g., `#ff0000`). Use Tailwind presets or CSS variables (`var(--accent-primary)`).
*   **Glassmorphism (毛玻璃)**: Use `backdrop-blur` with semi-transparent backgrounds for a premium feel.
    *   Example: `bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-md border border-white/20`
*   **Depth**: Use layered shadows (`shadow-xl`, `shadow-2xl`) to create depth. Avoid flat, boring designs.
*   **Non-Destructive**: Use soft notifications (Toasts) over hard Alerts unless critical.

### 交互与动画 (Interaction & Animation)
*   **No Rough Transitions**: All state changes (Hover, Layout, Show/Hide) must have smooth transitions.
    *   Standard: `transition-all duration-300 ease-out`
*   **Feedback**: Every user interaction must have visual feedback (Active scale, Ripple/Pulse, Color shift).

### 响应式 (Responsive)
*   **Mobile First**: Design for mobile constraints first, then adapt for desktop (`md:`, `lg:`).
*   **Touch Friendly**: Minimum 44px touch targets on mobile.

## 4. 目录结构规范 (Directory Structure)

*   `src/components`: Pure UI Components (stateless or UI-state only).
*   `src/components/common`: Atomic reusable components (Button, Input, Modal).
*   `src/context`: Global State Containers.
*   `src/hooks`: Custom Hooks.
*   `src/services`: Business Logic, API, Data Processing (**Core Refactor Area**).
*   `src/types`: Unified TS Types.
*   `src/utils`: Pure Functions (non-React).

## 5. 错误处理 (Error Handling)

*   **Defensive Coding**: Use Optional Chaining (`?.`) and Nullish Coalescing (`??`) for deep object access.
*   **User Feedback**: Translate API errors into friendly Chinese messages via `notificationService`.
*   **Logging**: Log critical errors with stack traces using `systemLogService.logError`.
